The paper deals with social media data and focuses on modeling users' interests and connections through shared images. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR) for recommendation and virality prediction, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) for connection discovery, Multimedia (cs.MM) for image analysis, Social Computing (cs.SOC) for social media applications, and Machine Learning (cs.LG) for the proposed model and algorithms. Among these, cs.IR and cs.SI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.MM, cs.SOC, and cs.LG.
